swMSTPMIB.name: swMSTPMIB
swMSTPMIB.description: The MIB module for managing MSTP.

swMSTPStpAdminState.name: swMSTPStpAdminState
swMSTPStpAdminState.description: This object indicates the spanning tree state of the bridge.

swMSTPStpVersion.name: swMSTPStpVersion
swMSTPStpVersion.description: The version of Spanning Tree Protocol the bridge is currently running.

swMSTPStpMaxAge.name: swMSTPStpMaxAge
swMSTPStpMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that the range for this parameter is related to the value of StpForwardDelay and PortAdminHelloTime. MaxAge <= 2(ForwardDelay - 1);MaxAge >= 2(HelloTime + 1) The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

swMSTPStpHelloTime.name: swMSTPStpHelloTime
swMSTPStpHelloTime.description: The value is used for HelloTime when this bridge is acting in RSTP or STP mode. Only in RSTP or STP mode can read/write this value.

swMSTPStpForwardDelay.name: swMSTPStpForwardDelay
swMSTPStpForwardDelay.description: This value, controls how long a port changes its spanning state from blocking to learning state and from learning to forwarding state. Note that the range for this parameter is related to MaxAge

swMSTPStpMaxHops.name: swMSTPStpMaxHops
swMSTPStpMaxHops.description: This value applies to all Spanning Trees within an MST Region for which the Bridge is the Regional Root.

swMSTPStpTxHoldCount.name: swMSTPStpTxHoldCount
swMSTPStpTxHoldCount.description: The value used by the Port Transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate.

swMSTPStpForwardBPDU.name: swMSTPStpForwardBPDU
swMSTPStpForwardBPDU.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to forward BPDU to non stp port.

swMSTPStpLBD.name: swMSTPStpLBD
swMSTPStpLBD.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to Loop-back prevention.

swMSTPStpLBDRecoverTime.name: swMSTPStpLBDRecoverTime
swMSTPStpLBDRecoverTime.description: The period of time(in second) on which STP module keeps checking the BPDU loop status, The valid range is 60 to 1000000 . If set this value from 1 to 59 will get 'bad value' return code. The value of zero is a special value which means to disable the auto-recovery mechanism for LBD feature.

swMSTPName.name: swMSTPName
swMSTPName.description: The object indicates the name of MST Configuration Identication.

swMSTPRevisionLevel.name: swMSTPRevisionLevel
swMSTPRevisionLevel.description: The object indicates the revision level of the MST Configuration Identification.

swMSTPInstanceCtrlTable.name: swMSTPInstanceCtrlTable
swMSTPInstanceCtrlTable.description: A table that contains MSTP instance information.

swMSTPInstId.name: swMSTPInstId
swMSTPInstId.description: This object indicates the specific instance. An MSTP Instance Id(MSTID) of zero is used to identify the CIST.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList1to64.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList1to64
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList1to64.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1-512) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList65to128.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList65to128
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList65to128.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (513-1024) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList129to192.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList129to192
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList129to192.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1025-1536) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList193to256.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList193to256
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList193to256.description: This object indicates the VLAN range(1537-2048) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList257to320.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList257to320
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList257to320.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2049-2560) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList321to384.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList321to384
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList321to384.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2561-3072) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList385to448.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList385to448
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList385to448.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3073-3584) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstVlanRangeList449to512.name: swMSTPInstVlanRangeList449to512
swMSTPInstVlanRangeList449to512.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3585-4096) that belongs to the instance.

swMSTPInstType.name: swMSTPInstType
swMSTPInstType.description: This object indicates the type of instance.

swMSTPInstStatus.name: swMSTPInstStatus
swMSTPInstStatus.description: The instance state that could be enabled/disabled.

swMSTPInstPriority.name: swMSTPInstPriority
swMSTPInstPriority.description: The priority of the instance. The priority must be dividable by 4096

swMSTPInstDesignatedRootBridge.name: swMSTPInstDesignatedRootBridge
swMSTPInstDesignatedRootBridge.description: The bridge identifier of the CIST. For MST instance, this object is unused.

swMSTPInstExternalRootCost.name: swMSTPInstExternalRootCost
swMSTPInstExternalRootCost.description: The path cost between MST Regions from the transmitting Bridge to the CIST Root. For MST instance this object is unused.

swMSTPInstRegionalRootBridge.name: swMSTPInstRegionalRootBridge
swMSTPInstRegionalRootBridge.description: For CIST, Regional Root Identifier is the Bridge Identifier of the single bridge in a Region whose CIST Root Port is a Boundary Port, or the Bridge Identifier of the CIST Root if that is within the Region; For MSTI,MSTI Regional Root Identifier is the Bridge Identifier of the MSTI Regional Root for this particular MSTI in this MST Region; The Regional Root Bridge of this instance.

swMSTPInstInternalRootCost.name: swMSTPInstInternalRootCost
swMSTPInstInternalRootCost.description: For CIST, the internal path cost is the path cost to the CIST Regional Root; For MSTI, the internal path cost is the path cost to the MSTI Regional Root for this particular MSTI in this MST Region

swMSTPInstDesignatedBridge.name: swMSTPInstDesignatedBridge
swMSTPInstDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier for the transmitting bridge for this CIST or MSTI

swMSTPInstRootPort.name: swMSTPInstRootPort
swMSTPInstRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the CIST or MSTI root bridge.

swMSTPInstMaxAge.name: swMSTPInstMaxAge
swMSTPInstMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

swMSTPInstForwardDelay.name: swMSTPInstForwardDelay
swMSTPInstForwardDelay.description: This value, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database.

swMSTPInstLastTopologyChange.name: swMSTPInstLastTopologyChange
swMSTPInstLastTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

swMSTPInstTopChangesCount.name: swMSTPInstTopChangesCount
swMSTPInstTopChangesCount.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

swMSTPInstRowStatus.name: swMSTPInstRowStatus
swMSTPInstRowStatus.description: This object indicates the RowStatus of this entry.

swMSTPPortTable.name: swMSTPPortTable
swMSTPPortTable.description: A table that contains port-specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

swMSTPPortEntry.name: swMSTPPortEntry
swMSTPPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that port.

swMSTPPort.name: swMSTPPort
swMSTPPort.description: The port number of the port for this entry.

swMSTPPortOperHelloTime.name: swMSTPPortOperHelloTime
swMSTPPortOperHelloTime.description: Is the actual value of the hello time.

swMSTPPortAdminHelloTime.name: swMSTPPortAdminHelloTime
swMSTPPortAdminHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of BPDU by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second.

swMSTPSTPPortEnable.name: swMSTPSTPPortEnable
swMSTPSTPPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

swMSTPPortExternalPathCost.name: swMSTPPortExternalPathCost
swMSTPPortExternalPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the CIST root which include this port.

swMSTPPortMigration.name: swMSTPPortMigration
swMSTPPortMigration.description: When operating in MSTP mode or RSTP mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this port to transmit MST BPDUs. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns FALSE(2) when read.

swMSTPPortAdminEdgePort.name: swMSTPPortAdminEdgePort
swMSTPPortAdminEdgePort.description: The value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of TRUE indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port and a value of FALSE indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port

swMSTPPortOperEdgePort.name: swMSTPPortOperEdgePort
swMSTPPortOperEdgePort.description: It is the acuture value of edge port status

swMSTPPortAdminP2P.name: swMSTPPortAdminP2P
swMSTPPortAdminP2P.description: The point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port.

swMSTPPortOperP2P.name: swMSTPPortOperP2P
swMSTPPortOperP2P.description: It is the acture value of P2P status.

swMSTPPortLBD.name: swMSTPPortLBD
swMSTPPortLBD.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to Loop-back prevention attached to this port.

swMSTPPortBPDUFiltering.name: swMSTPPortBPDUFiltering
swMSTPPortBPDUFiltering.description: The enabled/disabled status is used to BPDU Filtering attached to this port.

swMSTPPortRestrictedRole.name: swMSTPPortRestrictedRole
swMSTPPortRestrictedRole.description: If TRUE, causes the port not to be selected as Root Port for the CIST or any MSTI, even it has the best spanning tree priority vector.

swMSTPPortRestrictedTCN.name: swMSTPPortRestrictedTCN
swMSTPPortRestrictedTCN.description: If TRUE, causes the port not to propagate received topology change notifications and topology changes to other Ports.

swMSTPMstPortTable.name: swMSTPMstPortTable
swMSTPMstPortTable.description: A table that contains port-specific information for the MST Protocol.

swMSTPMstPortEntry.name: swMSTPMstPortEntry
swMSTPMstPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the MST state for that port.

swMSTPMstPort.name: swMSTPMstPort
swMSTPMstPort.description: The port number of the port for this entry.

swMSTPMstPortInsID.name: swMSTPMstPortInsID
swMSTPMstPortInsID.description: This object indicates the MSTP Instance Id(MSTID).

swMSTPMstPortInternalPathCost.name: swMSTPMstPortInternalPathCost
swMSTPMstPortInternalPathCost.description: This is the value of this port to the path cost of paths towards the MSTI root.

swMSTPMstPortPriority.name: swMSTPMstPortPriority
swMSTPMstPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID..

swMSTPMstPortStatus.name: swMSTPMstPortStatus
swMSTPMstPortStatus.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. If the PortEnable is disabled, the the port status will be no-stp-enabled(7); If the port is in error disabled status, the port status will be err-disable(8)

swMSTPMstPortRole.name: swMSTPMstPortRole
swMSTPMstPortRole.description: When the port Enable state is enabled, the port's current port role as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. If the Port Enable state is disabled, the the port role will be nonstp(5)
